Fine tuning - fine tuning is the process of adopting a pre-trained
model to perform better on specific, specialized tasks.So the model is already trained on large amounts of data, but needs to be optimized 
for domain specific knowledge. That means retrain an existing model with new data in order to improve performance on a specific task
with domain specific knowledge. Rather than trying to retrain a model from scratch, which would take enormous time and resources, fine tuning is a more
efficient way to tailor an existing model for a narrow domain.
Advantage - token savings due to shorter prompts, Fewer tokens means less data to process, which directly reduces latency.
And since most of the language model charts based on the number of tokens processed, reducing token usage can lead to lower API cost.

How Fine tuning works?
We will start with pre-trained LM to deploy fine tuned domain specific LM, and we have created five steps to understand how does fine tuning works.
1. And the first step is pre-trained LM.
2. So the next step is preparation the fine tuning dataset -  introducing a new dataset that is specific to the domain.This dataset is 
typically much smaller than the massive dataset used to pre-trained models. fine tuning dataset often includes labeled examples, 
which are used to train the model on specific tasks.
3. next step is training the model on new data - We should upload data for training and create the fine tuning job and then run that job.
This training process updates the model's internal parameters, its weights and biases, so it can adapt to the new context.
4. evaluation and optimization step - It is essential to evaluate its performance on the target tasks, so we test the fine tuned model using
the validation datasets.
5. Deloy step - The last step we can come to the deploying and maintenance when using the fine tuning model in your app.

Fine Tuning Methods - 
1. The first method is fully fine tuning, which involves adjusting all the parameters in the pre-trained
model to make it highly specialized for your task. In full fine tuning, the entire model's parameters, its weights and biases are updated based on the
fine tuning data set.
2. Parameter efficient fine tuning - which focuses on updating only a small subset of the model's parameters instead of the entire model.
paved requires less data and fewer computational resources.It particularly useful for resource constrained environments, or when you need to 
fine tune the model on specific, narrow tasks like improving customer sentiment analysis or adjusting tone or style
3. Low Rank Adaptation - It allows you to fine tune a model efficiently without retraining the entire model.
In LoRA, small trainable metrics are added to certain layers of the model. Because you are only training the edit matrices, 
the rest of the model remains unchanged. This significantly reduces the computational resources needed for fine tuning.
it has a diff version - Quantized LoRA(QLoRA) -  more memory efficient iteration of traditional LoRA.
QLoRA takes Laura a step further by also quantizing the weights of the Laura adapters, which is a similar matrices to the lower precision.
These further operation reduces the memory footprint and the storage requirements.
4. Transfer Learning - Transfer learning is about taking the knowledge a model has learned from one domain, like general language
understanding and transferring it to a different but related domain. Transfer learning is especially useful when you don't 
have enough labeled data to train a model from scratch in your domain.

Challenges fo Fine Tuning - 
1. Overfitting happens when a model becomes too focused on the specific data set used for the fine tuning.It performs well on 
that data, but poorly on unseen or real world task. One way to prevent overfitting is by using the regularization techniques 
like dropout or weight decay.
2.  another challenges could be fine tuning is the quality and the quantity of the data Fine tuning requires high quality data set.
3. Fine tuning can be resource incentive, especially if you are working with large models and datasets.Depending on the complexity 
of the task and the model, fine tuning can take hours or even days.

In order to address these challenges, consider using cloud based platforms like Google Cloud, AWS,
