These vectors are numerical representations that capture the semantic meaning of data.
It can be text, image, audio, or other type of information.
So a vector database indexes and stores vector embeddings for fast retrieval and similarity search.
For example, we can say that a search for mobile phone in a vector database would also retrieve results
for smartphone, even if the word smartphone was not explicitly mentioned in the query.
So this ability to understand context and meaning unlock the powerful applications like semantic search,
personalized recommendation, and more.
